info.title: Web Search
info.description: The comprehensive web search API, powered by Google Search.

parameters.name: exact
parameters.description: Identifies a phrase that all documents in the search results must contain.

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description:
Restricts the search to documents written in a particular language (e.g., lr=lang_ja).

Acceptable values are:

- \\\"lang_ar\\\": Arabic
- \\\"lang_bg\\\": Bulgarian
- \\\"lang_ca\\\": Catalan
- \\\"lang_cs\\\": Czech
- \\\"lang_da\\\": Danish
- \\\"lang_de\\\": German
- \\\"lang_el\\\": Greek
- \\\"lang_en\\\": English
- \\\"lang_es\\\": Spanish
- \\\"lang_et\\\": Estonian
- \\\"lang_fi\\\": Finnish
- \\\"lang_fr\\\": French
- \\\"lang_hr\\\": Croatian
- \\\"lang_hu\\\": Hungarian
- \\\"lang_id\\\": Indonesian
- \\\"lang_is\\\": Icelandic
- \\\"lang_it\\\": Italian
- \\\"lang_iw\\\": Hebrew
- \\\"lang_ja\\\": Japanese
- \\\"lang_ko\\\": Korean
- \\\"lang_lt\\\": Lithuanian
- \\\"lang_lv\\\": Latvian
- \\\"lang_nl\\\": Dutch
- \\\"lang_no\\\": Norwegian
- \\\"lang_pl\\\": Polish
- \\\"lang_pt\\\": Portuguese
- \\\"lang_ro\\\": Romanian
- \\\"lang_ru\\\": Russian
- \\\"lang_sk\\\": Slovak
- \\\"lang_sl\\\": Slovenian
- \\\"lang_sr\\\": Serbian
- \\\"lang_sv\\\": Swedish
- \\\"lang_tr\\\": Turkish
- \\\"lang_zh-CN\\\": Chinese (Simplified)
- \\\"lang_zh-TW\\\": Chinese (Traditional)

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: num
parameters.description:
Number of search results to return.

Valid values are integers between 1 and 10, inclusive.

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: cache
parameters.description: See Google’s cached version of a site. See [here](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/2466433?hl=en) for details.

parameters.name: social
parameters.description: Search social media. See [here](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/2466433?hl=en) for details.

parameters.name: safe
parameters.description:
Search safety level. Acceptable values are:

- 'active': Enables SafeSearch filtering.
- 'off': Disables SafeSearch filtering. (default)

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: site
parameters.description: Specifies a given site which should always be included or excluded from results (see siteSearchFilter parameter, below).

parameters.name: related
parameters.description: Specifies that all search results should be pages that are related to the specified URL.

parameters.name: price
parameters.description: Search related to the price of the query item (in USD). See [here](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/2466433?hl=en) for details.

parameters.name: daterestrict
parameters.description:
Restricts results to URLs based on date. Supported values include:

- d[number]: requests results from the specified number of past days.
- w[number]: requests results from the specified number of past weeks.
- m[number]: requests results from the specified number of past months.
- y[number]: requests results from the specified number of past years.

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: gl
parameters.description:
Geolocation of end user.

- The gl parameter value is a two-letter country code. The gl parameter boosts search results whose country of origin matches the parameter value. See the [Country Codes](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/docs/xml_results_appendices#countryCodes) page for a list of valid values.
- Specifying a gl parameter value should lead to more relevant results. This is particularly true for international customers and, even more specifically, for customers in English- speaking countries other than the United States.

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Each page consists of 10 results. Google provides up to a maximum of 10 pages of results. Page can take on values between 1-10 as a result.

parameters.name: cr
parameters.description:
Restricts search results to documents originating in a particular country. You may use [Boolean operators](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/docs/xml_results_appendices#booleanOperators) in the cr parameter's value.

Google Search determines the country of a document by analyzing:

- the top-level domain (TLD) of the document's URL
- the geographic location of the Web server's IP address

See the [Country Parameter Values](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/docs/xml_results_appendices#countryCollections) page for a list of valid values for this parameter.

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: exclude
parameters.description: Exclude words from your search. See [here](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/2466433?hl=en) for details.

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description:
The sort expression to apply to the results. The sort parameter specifies that the results be sorted according to the specified expression i.e. sort by date. [Example: sort=date.](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/docs/structured_search#sort-by-attribute)

See [here](https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/reference/rest/v1/cse/list#http-request) for details.

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: The free text query to conduct a web search for.

get.description: Conducts a comprehensive web search based on a free text query.
